The paper deals with the topic of knowledge transfer between AI systems, which is a common problem in machine learning and artificial intelligence. The paper specifically discusses the transfer of knowledge from a pre-trained convolutional neural network to a simple linear classifier with HOG features, which falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV). However, the paper also discusses the structure of the internal variables of the AI system, which is a topic related to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of linear functionals, which is a topic related to numerical analysis (cs.NA) and control systems (cs.SY). Overall, the most likely categories are cs.LG, cs.AI, and cs.CV, with cs.NE and cs.SY being less likely but still possible.
